questionTemplates.text:
M: How are you getting on with your essay, Mary? I'm having areal hard time with mine.
W: After two sleepless nights, I'm finally through with it.
{a}

W: We should spend this weekend in Hangzhou.
M: How about the whole week?
{a}

W: How old are you now?
M: I'm twenty-eight years old.
{a}

M: I'd like to drive to the concert,but my brother will use the car tonight.
W: Who needs a car?We can take the bus if we go a little earlier.
{a}

W: The doctor told me not to smoke anymore.
M: I think he is right.
{a}

M: Is there anything else you want to buy while we are in town?
W: Let's stop at the cantata shop to get some color films. I want to take some pictures in our garden today.
{a}

M: I like science more than maths, but history is my favorite subject.
W: But I think computer programming is the best.
{a}

W: Why didn't you come here yesterday, John?
M: I'm sorry, madam. My mother was ill.
{a}

M: I'm looking for an unfurnished two-bedroom apartment, but all your apartments are furnished.
W: We can take care of that. We can simply remove the furniture.
{a}

W: Can you speak English?
M: Certainly, and I can also speak Japanese and Chinese.
{a}

M: Todd got the highest grade point in the biology class.
W: No wonder! He's at the library every day.
{a}

F: Look at the clock. We'll be late.
M: The film will start at 8: 30. It's 8:00 now.
{a}

W: Renting a Conference Room at the hotel will cost us too much. We are already running in the red
M: How about using our dining room for the meeting?
{a}

W: Excuse me. Do you know when the train will arrive?
M: I'm sorry. The train is behind schedule. You have to wait another twenty minutes.
{a}

M: I often listen to light music at home. What kind of music do you like?
W: I really enjoy Chinese music.
{a}

F: I think it is going to rain, Jack.
M: I don't think so, Jane. The radio said it is going to be fine soon.
{a}

M: Look at that dark cloud. I am afraid it's going to rain.
W: I don't think so. The weather report says it will be fine today.
{a}

M: These cabbages look so good, and they're only 30 cents a pound.
W: Let's get some beans. And how about some peas, too?
{a}

M: I like the way you've done your hair, dear. It looks so natural and original.
W: Thank you. I am surprised you noticed it.
{a}

W: I want a ticket for the concert tomorrow. How much is it?
M: I'm sorry., there are no tickets left for tomorrow. But we still have two for Friday.
{a}

W: I really can't stand the way David controls the conversation all the time. If he's going to be at the Christmas party, I just won't come.
M: I'm sorry you feel that way. But my mother insists that he come.
{a}

F: Would you mind turning off the radio?
M: Sure, of course I will.
{a}

M: This car is for your birthday.
W: Thank you very much. What a lovely car!
{a}

W: How long will it take you to fix my radio?
M: I'll call you when it is ready,but it won't take any longer than a week.
{a}
